message.content:
1. The baseline assessment was conducted in September 2010.
2. 53 classes from 45 primary schools in Lower Austria were involved in the study.
3. The classes were randomly assigned to different groups.
4. There were two groups: an intervention group and a waiting control group.
5. The intervention group consisted of 26 classes.
6. The intervention group had 432 children.
7. The waiting control group consisted of 27 classes.
8. The waiting control group had 493 children.
9. The children in the study were approximately 8.7 years old.
10. The age range of the children in the study was approximately +/- 4 months around 8.7 years.

messages.content:
Statement: After baseline assessment in September 2010, 53 classes from 45 primary schools in Lower Austria were randomly assigned to an intervention (n = 26 classes, 432 children) or waiting control arm (n = 27 classes, 493 children aged 8.7 years +/- 4 months).
